cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DB 

This paper is about using Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) for industrial applications such as search engine and online advertising systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the development of a distributed system for learning big LDA models from big data, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are covered by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the use of big data, which is relevant to cs.DB (Databases).
